Title : Gunnar Handal
Text : '''Gunnar Handal''' (born 25 March 1936) is a [[Norway|Norwegian]] educationalist.

He was born in [[Bergen]]. He took the [[mag.art.]] degree in [[pedagogy]] at the [[University of Oslo]] in 1964, but was hired at {{lang|no|Pedagogisk forskningsintstitutt}} (now: the Department of Education) at the University of Oslo already in 1963. From 1992 to his retirement he served as professor of university pedagogy. He had then led the "Study Quality Committee" from 1989 to 1990, which highlighted quality in university studies. In 2003 he was awarded the Kristian Ottosen Prize for promoting student welfare.<ref name=ntb>{{cite news|title=Gunnar Handal 60 år 25. mars|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=6 March 1996|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Pedagog for kvalitet|last=Lippestad|first=Jenny|date=25 March 1996|work=Aftenposten|page=10|language=Norwegian}}</ref><ref name=ntb2>{{cite news|title=70 år 25. mars: Professor Gunnar Handal|agency=Norwegian News Agency|date=10 March 2006|language=Norwegian}}</ref>

He resides at [[Grav, Norway|Grav]].<ref name=ntb2/>

